            . I live at Hampstead, and <rs id="t18231022-77-viclabel430" type="occupation">let out horses and chaise</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231022-77-victim716 t18231022-77-viclabel430"></join>; the prisoner was employed to drive Mrs. Stodhart, from Hampstead to Finchly, and back for 6 s., on the 30th of August, and to receive the money - the chaise went father than was agreed upon. I never saw him or the horse and chaise till Monday morning, when I found it at the Bull, public-house, at Highgate, and had 3 s. to pay.</p>
               <p>DR. 
               <persName id="t18231022-77-person717">
                  JOHN 
                  STODHART
               <interp inst="t18231022-77-person717" type="surname" value="STODHART"></interp>
