                  </persName>
            . On the 30th of August, I was at Finchly, and saw my lady in the chaise - she told me to pay the prisoner 8 s., which I did, and 1 s. for himself.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The horse was knocked up, and I put up at the Bull, was going home next morning with the money, got drunk and lost it.</p>
